<td>3 consistently scaling</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Retargeting Conversion Share</td>
<td>12%</td>
<td>34%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Test Creative Survival Rate</td>
<td>8%</td>
<td>22%</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h2>Action Checklist for Independent Website Sellers</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Check data before allocating</strong>: run at least 2 weeks of baseline data before setting allocation ratios</li>
<li><strong>Set aside 10% flexible funds</strong>: to handle algorithm fluctuations or sudden creative opportunities</li>
<li><strong>Check each campaign's spend weekly</strong>: adjust immediately when budget caps are hit</li>
<li><strong>Don't skimp on retargeting budget</strong>: this is the most effective way to cut costs and increase efficiency for independent websites</li>
<li><strong>Build a budget allocation SOP</strong>: the smaller the team, the more you need standardized processes to reduce trial-and-error costs</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<p>There's no standard answer for budget allocation, but one thing is certain: <strong>replacing "gut feeling" with "data" and "even distribution" with "stratified spending" is the first step from burning money to making money in independent website advertising.</strong></p>
